olive oil
2 potato
20 g butter
2 tbs milk
1 bag baby broccoli
1 carrot
1 packet pork loin steaks
½ bottle cream
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 clove garlic
1 sachet All-American Spice Blend

• Boil the kettle. Half-fill a large saucepan with
boiling water.
• Peel potato and cut into large chunks.
• Cook potato in the boiling water over high heat,
until easily pierced with a fork, 12-15 minutes.
Drain and return to the pan.
• Add the butter and milk to potato and season
generously with salt. Mash until smooth. Cover
to keep warm.

TIP: Save time and get more fibre by leaving the
potato unpeeled.

• Meanwhile, trim baby broccoli. Slice carrot into
thin sticks. Finely chop garlic.
• In a medium bowl, combine pork loin steaks,
1/2 the All-American spice blend, a drizzle of
olive oil and a pinch of salt.

• Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat
with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook baby broccoli
and carrot, tossing, until tender,
5-6 minutes.
• Add garlic and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.
Season with salt and pepper. Transfer to a
medium bowl and cover to keep warm.

• Return the frying pan to medium-high heat with
a drizzle of olive oil. When oil is hot, cook pork
until cooked through, 3-4 minutes each side
(depending on thickness). Transfer to a plate and
set aside to rest.

TIP: Don't worry if the spice blend chars a little in
the pan, this adds to the flavour!

• Wipe out and return the frying pan to medium
heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Add the remaining
All-American spice blend and cook, stirring,
until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Stir through cream (see ingredients),
chicken-style stock powder and any pork
resting juices and simmer until thickened
slightly, 1-2 minutes.

• Thickly slice pork.
• Divide potato mash, veggies and pan-fried pork
between plates.
• Spoon over All-American sauce to serve. Enjoy!